KEY ML-1.1 / B2030B-1.0 CLARIFICATIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- REINFORCING LAYER (§C.0, §1.5): The Ethical-Use Conditions are a reinforcing
  and remedial layer, not a freestanding source of novel prohibitions. Their
  primary effect is to ground TERMINATION and scope-of-grant. The PRIMARY
  protection for this software is its structural/technical safeguards
  (capability-based security, sandboxing, default-deny, post-quantum crypto, the
  AI redaction pipeline, the per-origin privacy budget) — this license is the
  fallback when those are absent, bypassed, or insufficient. No greater
  enforceability is claimed than the forum's law allows.

- FINANCIAL FUNCTIONALITY EXPRESSLY PERMITTED (§C.8): Browser 2030B ships no
  first-party financial features, but the license expressly PERMITS Financial
  Functionality (currency, ledgers, payments, lending, yield, demurrage, custody,
  etc.) for any downstream/extension/web use. The Riba norm is interpretive only
  and never renders lawful financial use non-compliant; doubt resolves in favor
  of permission.

- NETWORK USE (§B.6): Only the sync server (sync/) and the WASM cloud edition
  (cloud/wasm-edition) can be "Network-Facing Works." If you deploy a MODIFIED
  version of one of those to remote users, you must offer them the Corresponding
  Network Source (operational secrets/keys may be redacted per §B.6.5). The
  shipped browser, installers, mobile apps, and engine copies are "Conveyed Copy
  Works" and carry no network-source obligation.

